data.current_description: Creates a sink that exports trace spans to a destination. The export of newly-ingested traces begins immediately, unless the sink's `writer_identity` is not permitted to write to the destination. A sink can export traces only from the resource owning the sink (the 'parent').
data.summary_suggestion: Create a trace sink for export
data.description_suggestion: Creates a new trace sink that exports trace spans to a specified destination. Requires a TraceSink object with output configuration. Trace export begins immediately upon creation, unless the sink's writer_identity lacks write permissions to the destination. The sink can only export traces from its parent resource (GCP project). Returns the created TraceSink object with assigned writer_identity.
